      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from enum import Enum\n\nclass FinishStatus(Enum):\n    OK = \"stop\"\n    TRUNCATED = \"length\"\n    FILTERED = \"content_filter\"\n    TOOL_CALL = \"tool_calls\"\n\n\ndef check_finish_reason(resp) -> tuple[str | None, FinishStatus | None]:\n    \"\"\"Returns (content, status) or (None, status) on non-stop.\"\"\"\n    choice = resp.choices[0]\n    reason = choice.finish_reason\n    text = choice.message.content or \"\"\n\n    if reason == \"stop\":\n        return text, FinishStatus.OK\n    elif reason == \"length\":\n        # Content is partial — caller must decide whether to continue\n        return text, FinishStatus.TRUNCATED\n    elif reason == \"content_filter\":\n        return None, FinishStatus.FILTERED\n    else:\n        return text, None\n\n\nresp = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o\",\n    messages=messages,\n    max_tokens=512,\n)\ntext, status = check_finish_reason(resp)\n\nif status == FinishStatus.TRUNCATED:\n    continuation = continue_generation(messages, partial_text=text)\n    text = text + continuation\nelif status == FinishStatus.FILTERED:\n    text = \"I can't help with that.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting Repetition Loops"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Repetition loops happen when the model gets stuck generating the same token sequence. They are most common at high temperature (above 1.0), with very long "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "max_tokens"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", or when the context window is near capacity. The signal is a high n-gram repetition ratio — the same substring appearing far more often than statistical chance predicts."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from collections import Counter\n\ndef repetition_score(text: str, n: int = 6) -> float:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns 0.0 (no repetition) to 1.0 (fully repetitive).\n    Uses character n-gram overlap: counts unique vs total n-grams.\n    \"\"\"\n    if len(text) < n * 2:\n        return 0.0\n    ngrams = [text[i:i+n] for i in range(len(text) - n + 1)]\n    if not ngrams:\n        return 0.0\n    unique = len(set(ngrams))\n    total = len(ngrams)\n    # High ratio of duplicates = high repetition\n    return 1.0 - (unique / total)\n\n\nREPETITION_THRESHOLD = 0.6   # 60% of 6-grams are duplicates → degenerate\n\n\ndef is_repetitive(text: str) -> bool:\n    score = repetition_score(text)\n    if score > REPETITION_THRESHOLD:\n        print(f\"[degenerate] Repetition score {score:.2f} exceeds threshold\")\n        return True\n    return False\n\n\n# Quick example\nlooping = \"The answer is yes. The answer is yes. The answer is yes.\"\nnormal  = \"The capital of France is Paris, a city on the Seine.\"\nprint(repetition_score(looping))  # ~0.78\nprint(repetition_score(normal))   # ~0.18"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Validating Structured Outputs with Pydantic"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you need JSON output, the model may return valid JSON that violates your schema, JSON wrapped in markdown fences, or plain text instead of JSON. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "instructor"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " library wraps any OpenAI-compatible client and automatically retries on schema validation failures, feeding the error back into the prompt so the model can self-correct."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import instructor\nfrom openai import OpenAI\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\nfrom typing import Literal\n\nclient = instructor.from_openai(OpenAI())\n\n\nclass SentimentResult(BaseModel):\n    sentiment: Literal[\"positive\", \"negative\", \"neutral\"]\n    confidence: float = Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    reason: str = Field(min_length=10, max_length=200)\n\n    @field_validator(\"reason\")\n    @classmethod\n    def reason_must_reference_sentiment(cls, v: str, info) -> str:\n        sentiment = info.data.get(\"sentiment\", \"\")\n        if sentiment and sentiment not in v.lower() and not any(\n            word in v.lower() for word in [\"positive\", \"negative\", \"neutral\", \"good\", \"bad\", \"mixed\"]\n        ):\n            raise ValueError(\"Reason must mention the sentiment or related terms\")\n        return v\n\n\ndef analyze_sentiment(text: str) -> SentimentResult | None:\n    try:\n        result = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n            response_model=SentimentResult,\n            max_retries=3,  # instructor retries with the validation error in context\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"Analyze the sentiment of the text.\"},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": text},\n            ],\n        )\n        return result\n    except instructor.exceptions.InstructorRetryException as e:\n        # Failed all retries — log and return None\n        print(f\"[schema] Failed after {e.n_attempts} attempts: {e.last_completion}\")\n        return None\n\n\n# Without instructor — manual fallback\nimport json\n\ndef parse_json_output(raw: str) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Strip markdown fences and parse JSON; return None on failure.\"\"\"\n    # Remove ```json ... ``` wrappers the model sometimes adds\n    stripped = raw.strip().removeprefix(\"```json\").removeprefix(\"```\").removesuffix(\"```\").strip()\n    try:\n        return json.loads(stripped)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        print(f\"[schema] JSON parse failed: {e}\")\n        return None"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Continuing Truncated Responses"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "finish_reason"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "\"length\""
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the model ran out of token budget mid-generation. You can continue generation by sending the partial output back as an assistant message and prompting the model to continue:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def complete_truncated(\n    original_messages: list[dict],\n    partial_text: str,\n    model: str = \"gpt-4o\",\n    max_rounds: int = 3,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    If a response was cut off (finish_reason=length), continue it.\n    Sends the partial text back as an assistant turn and asks for continuation.\n    \"\"\"\n    accumulated = partial_text\n    messages = original_messages + [\n        {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": partial_text}\n    ]\n\n    for round_num in range(max_rounds):\n        continuation_prompt = messages + [\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Please continue exactly where you left off.\"}\n        ]\n        resp = await client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=model,\n            messages=continuation_prompt,\n            max_tokens=512,\n        )\n        new_text = resp.choices[0].message.content or \"\"\n        accumulated += new_text\n\n        if resp.choices[0].finish_reason == \"stop\":\n            break\n        # Still truncated — continue\n        messages = continuation_prompt + [{\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": new_text}]\n\n    return accumulated\n\n\n# Usage\nresp = await client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o\", messages=messages, max_tokens=200\n)\ntext = resp.choices[0].message.content or \"\"\nif resp.choices[0].finish_reason == \"length\":\n    text = await complete_truncated(messages, text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-Grading for Coherence and Relevance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For high-stakes outputs where you cannot verify correctness by schema, use a second cheap model call to grade the response before returning it to the user. This is sometimes called \"LLM-as-judge\" or self-grading."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from pydantic import BaseModel\nimport instructor\n\ngrader_client = instructor.from_openai(OpenAI())\n\n\nclass GradeResult(BaseModel):\n    answers_question: bool\n    is_coherent: bool\n    score: int  # 1–5\n    issue: str | None  # None if no issue\n\n\nGRADE_SYSTEM = \"\"\"\nYou are a strict output quality judge. Given a user question and an AI response,\nassess whether the response actually answers the question and is coherent.\nBe conservative — if in doubt, mark answers_question=false.\n\"\"\"\n\n\ndef grade_response(question: str, response: str) -> GradeResult:\n    return grader_client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",  # cheap model for grading\n        response_model=GradeResult,\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": GRADE_SYSTEM},\n            {\n                \"role\": \"user\",\n                \"content\": f\"Question: {question}\\n\\nAI Response: {response}\",\n            },\n        ],\n    )\n\n\ndef validated_response(\n    question: str,\n    candidate: str,\n    fallback: str = \"I'm not sure. Please try rephrasing your question.\",\n) -> str:\n    grade = grade_response(question, candidate)\n    if grade.answers_question and grade.is_coherent and grade.score >= 3:\n        return candidate\n    print(f\"[grade] Rejected (score={grade.score}): {grade.issue}\")\n    return fallback"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A Unified Output Validation Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In practice, combine these checks into a single validation step that runs before any response reaches the user:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom enum import Enum\n\nclass DegenerateType(Enum):\n    TRUNCATED = \"truncated\"\n    FILTERED = \"filtered\"\n    REPETITIVE = \"repetitive\"\n    EMPTY = \"empty\"\n    SCHEMA_FAIL = \"schema_fail\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass ValidationResult:\n    ok: bool\n    text: str | None\n    degenerate_type: DegenerateType | None\n    raw: str\n\n\ndef validate_output(\n    resp,\n    min_length: int = 20,\n    max_length: int = 10_000,\n    rep_threshold: float = 0.6,\n) -> ValidationResult:\n    choice = resp.choices[0]\n    raw = choice.message.content or \"\"\n    reason = choice.finish_reason\n\n    # 1. finish_reason\n    if reason == \"content_filter\":\n        return ValidationResult(ok=False, text=None, degenerate_type=DegenerateType.FILTERED, raw=raw)\n    if reason == \"length\":\n        return ValidationResult(ok=False, text=raw, degenerate_type=DegenerateType.TRUNCATED, raw=raw)\n\n    # 2. Empty check\n    if len(raw.strip()) < min_length:\n        return ValidationResult(ok=False, text=None, degenerate_type=DegenerateType.EMPTY, raw=raw)\n\n    # 3. Repetition check\n    if is_repetitive(raw) or len(raw) > max_length:\n        return ValidationResult(ok=False, text=None, degenerate_type=DegenerateType.REPETITIVE, raw=raw)\n\n    # 4. All clear\n    return ValidationResult(ok=True, text=raw, degenerate_type=None, raw=raw)\n\n\nasync def safe_generate(messages: list[dict]) -> str:\n    resp = await client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"gpt-4o\", messages=messages, max_tokens=512\n    )\n    result = validate_output(resp)\n\n    if result.ok:\n        return result.text\n\n    if result.degenerate_type == DegenerateType.TRUNCATED:\n        return await complete_truncated(messages, result.raw)\n\n    if result.degenerate_type == DegenerateType.REPETITIVE:\n        # Retry with a lower temperature and explicit repetition penalty\n        retry_resp = await client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o\",\n            messages=messages,\n            max_tokens=512,\n            temperature=0.3,\n            frequency_penalty=0.8,\n        )\n        retry_result = validate_output(retry_resp)\n        if retry_result.ok:\n            return retry_result.text\n\n    # All recovery attempts failed — return a safe default\n    return \"I wasn't able to generate a useful response. Please try again.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Adjusting Generation Parameters to Reduce Degenerate Outputs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Some degenerate outputs are preventable by tuning the generation parameters before the call rather than fixing them after:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "frequency_penalty (0–2):"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " reduces the probability of tokens that have already appeared. Values of 0.5–1.0 significantly cut repetition loops without degrading coherence."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "presence_penalty (0–2):"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " adds a one-time penalty to any token that has appeared, encouraging the model to explore new vocabulary. More aggressive than frequency_penalty."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
